Tenant Controller

Base URL: /api/tenants

1. Create a Tenant
Endpoint: /api/tenants
Method: POST
Description: Creates a new tenant.

Request Body:
`json`
{
  "id": <Long>,              // (optional) ID of the tenant
  "name": <String>,          // Name of the tenant
  "email": <String>,         // Email address of the tenant
  "phone": <String>,         // (optional) Phone number of the tenant
  "address": <String>,       // (optional) Address of the tenant
  "createdAt": <String>,     // (optional) Timestamp of creation
  "updatedAt": <String>      // (optional) Timestamp of last update
}
Response:
Status Code: 201 Created
Body: Returns the created tenant.
`json`
{
  "id": <Long>,
  "name": <String>,
  "email": <String>,
  "phone": <String>,
  "address": <String>,
  "createdAt": <String>,
  "updatedAt": <String>
}

2. Update a Tenant
Endpoint: /api/tenants/{tenantId}
Method: PUT
Description: Updates an existing tenant.

Path Parameter: tenantId (Long): The ID of the tenant to update.
Request Body:
`json`
{
  "name": <String>,          // Updated name of the tenant
  "email": <String>,         // Updated email of the tenant
  "phone": <String>,         // Updated phone number
  "address": <String>        // Updated address
}
Response:
Status Code: 200 OK
Body: Returns the updated tenant.
`json`
{
  "id": <Long>,
  "name": <String>,
  "email": <String>,
  "phone": <String>,
  "address": <String>,
  "createdAt": <String>,
  "updatedAt": <String>
}

3. Get a Tenant by ID
Endpoint: /api/tenants/{tenantId}
Method: GET
Description: Retrieves a specific tenant by its ID.

Path Parameter: tenantId (Long): The ID of the tenant to retrieve.
Response:
Status Code: 200 OK
Body:
`json`
{
  "id": <Long>,
  "name": <String>,
  "email": <String>,
  "phone": <String>,
  "address": <String>,
  "createdAt": <String>,
  "updatedAt": <String>
}
Status Code: 404 Not Found
Returns no body if the tenant is not found.

4. Get All Tenants
Endpoint: /api/tenants
Method: GET
Description: Retrieves a list of all tenants.

Response:
Status Code: 200 OK
Body: Returns a list of all tenants.
`json`
[
  {
    "id": <Long>,
    "name": <String>,
    "email": <String>,
    "phone": <String>,
    "address": <String>,
    "createdAt": <String>,
    "updatedAt": <String>
  },
  ...
]

5. Delete a Tenant
Endpoint: /api/tenants/{tenantId}
Method: DELETE
Description: Deletes a specific tenant by its ID.

Path Parameter: tenantId (Long): The ID of the tenant to delete.
Response:
Status Code: 204 No Content
